main event: A single yellowish-white object was observed over Columbus, Ohio on January 14, 1956.
interesting points: The object appeared to be at a high altitude and moved rapidly, making no sound.
The sighting lasted for 3-5 minutes on a clear night with no identifiable aircraft traffic.
A second sighting occurred in Columbus, Ohio on October 16, 1953, with a duration of 2 minutes.
The second sighting was concluded to possibly or probably be a balloon.
The report mentions a 'RED TEAM WHITE AREA C DR. ROEDUP' and other references to military/intelligence entities.
